    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated salmon</strong> and and cook for 9-10 min, turning once halfway, or until golden and cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>salmon</strong> to a plate, cover loosely with<strong> tin foil</strong> and set aside</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
